  "texts": [
    "The cells were washed once in 0.1% BSA in PBS and incubated overnight with the primary antibody diluted in PBS containing 1% BSA at 4 °C (anti-MAP2, 1:1,000 and anti-CHAT, 1:200; Abcam, ab92434 and ab6168, respectively).",
    "After three washes in PBS containing 0.1% BSA, the cells were incubated with the secondary antibody diluted in PBS containing 1% BSA for 1 h at room temperature (goat anti-rabbit A633, 1:500 and goat anti-chicken A488, 1:2,000; Thermo Fisher Scientific, A-21070 and A-11039, respectively), followed by another three washes with 1% BSA in PBS-0.05% Tween-20, with DAPI added during the second wash step (1:1,000).",
    "Cardiomyocytes were blocked and permeabilized in blocking solution (3% BSA and 0.1% Triton X-100 in PBS) for 1 h at room temperature.",
    "After three washes with PBS-0.1% Tween-20, the cells were incubated overnight at 4 °C with primary antibody (anti-ɑ-actinin-2, Sigma-Aldrich, A7811, 1:800 and anti-cardiac troponin T, CT3, deposited to the DSHB by Lin, J. J.",
    "-C., 1:5) diluted in staining solution (1% BSA and 0.1% Tween in PBS)."
